## Key Considerations
- **Error Handling**: Hook must ALWAYS return \`{"decision": "continue"}\` even on error - never block user
- **Performance**: Keep analysis <100ms - limit to top 3 skills to avoid context overload
- **Priority Sorting**: critical > high > medium > low, then process > domain > workflow
- **Debug Mode**: Use DEBUG_HOOKS=true environment variable for troubleshooting
- **Pattern Safety**: All regex patterns in skill-rules.json use lazy quantifiers to avoid catastrophic backtracking
- **Graceful Degradation**: If skill-rules.json missing or malformed, return continue with no context
- **JSON Output**: Must output valid JSON to stdout - errors go to stderr

## Anti-patterns to Avoid
- ‚ùå Blocking user if hook fails (always return decision: continue)
- ‚ùå Loading skill-rules.json on every pattern check (load once at start)
- ‚ùå Activating too many skills (limit to 3 to avoid context pollution)
- ‚ùå Forgetting to make script executable (chmod +x)
- ‚ùå Hardcoding paths instead of using __dirname and path.join
- ‚ùå Not handling malformed JSON input gracefully
- ‚ùå Using synchronous file operations in hot path (acceptable here since once per prompt)
- ‚ùå Assuming Node.js modules available (only use built-in: fs, path)
